QUESTION 1

Provide a brief overview (2-4 sentences) of the dataset. (It is always good practice to start an analysis by getting a feel for the data and providing a quick summary for readers.) You do not need to show any source code for this question, although you probably want to use code to get information.

ggplot(data = hiphop) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = ethnic))

Summarizing the data by ethnicity, this study is overwhelmingly white which does not seem like an even distribution of races to conduct a proper study. The smallest groups of ethnicities are biracial, black, native and unknown. Asian is the second highest ethnic group.

Clean the dataset in whichever ways you see fit.

hiphop_clean <- hiphop %>%

  sex = as.factor(as.character(sex)),

  ethnic = as.factor(as.character(ethnic)))

QUESTION 4

Make a new variable that recategorizes ethnic into only two groups, white and non-white, to simplify your data.

Helpful functions: mutate(), case_when()

hiphop_clean <- hiphop_clean %>% 
  mutate(clean_ethnic = case_when(
      ethnic == 'white' ~ 'white',
      ethnic != 'white' ~ 'non white'
    )
  )

hiphop_clean <- hiphop_clean %>% 
  mutate(
  clean_ethnic = as.factor(as.character(clean_ethnic)))

QUESTION 1

Aubrey hopes that his songs will be percieved as authentically hiphop. He hopes his lyrics will be recognizeable to those who describe themselves as hiphop fans, but less recognizeable to those who do not consider themselves fans. Suggest some words or phrases that Aubrey should try to use, and some words he should avoid.

Hint: Do not simply find the most popular words in each category. Think about words that are very different between hiphop fans and nonfans.

hiphop_clean %>% 
  filter(hiphop == 10) %>% 
  group_by(word, hiphop) %>% 
  summarize(meantop = mean(familiarity, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(hiphop)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  top_n(1, meantop)

I first filtered the data for words for hip hop fans (those who filled out a 10 under favorability of hip hop) I then grouped it by word and found the most popular words (with the highest rating on average being 5). The words that are most popular for hip hop fans are listed below.

most popular words for hiphop fans: ashy cuddie feel me player hater toe up what it do

I did the same thing for finding most popularly known words for non hip hop fans by filtering the hiphop variable for 0. I found the top 5 words and those are listed below. These words should not be used as if Aubrey does not want non hip hop fans to recognize his music, he should only be using words distinct to hip hop fans alone.

most popular words for non hiphop fans: off the hook feel me boo hella

Since feel me is in both categories, this word should also be avoided using as non hip hop fans will recognize this word.

QUESTION 3

Aubreys true life dream is to collaborate with his fellow Canadian musician Justin Bieber. Luckily, he knows that Bieber himself was one of the subjects in this study! You know that Bieber is a white male, aged 17-23 at the time of the study, from a relatively small town (10,000-60,000 people) in Ontario.

Determine which subject is secretly Bieber, and justify your answer.

Hint: Refer again to the dataset description. There is another clue about Biebers identity.

hiphop_clean %>%

My thought process with this question was to filter the data by the bieber condition at the max value as a true Justin Beiber (one who knows a lot of songs by him), would be the most inclined to hear a song featuring him. I then filtered the hip hop category to be greater than or equal to 8 as that was the max rating of hip hop liking for the previously filtered justin bieber inclined subjects. I then filtered familiarity to be equal to 5 as that was the highest level option for rating hip hop songs - we want people who (1) like hip hop and (2) recognize most of the words listed as they will resonate with them more when listed in the song titles. After that, I grouped the data by word then cleaned it to only show the distinct words. I was left with 26 unique words in which I randomly arranged to make song titles.
